My prompt: now i want a statistical test specifically for the proxy account hypothesis, test whether the alpha distribution is different between proxy accounts like spouse and joint vs direct self accounts, I want you do this beacause senators might did suspicious trades through family members

AI response: I have implemented a Welch's independent-samples t-test comparing the distribution of market-adjusted alpha between transactions executed through proxy accounts (spouse, joint, dependent child) and those executed directly by the senator. This test operationalises one of the project's core hypotheses: if senators route informed trades through distanced accounts to reduce personal scrutiny, the alpha on proxy transactions should be systematically higher than on self-executed ones. The visualization overlays the two alpha histograms with vertical dashed lines at their respective means, making any distributional shift immediately visible.

